OL,4,Cthird most-used appliance
OL,6,FThe study also found that 60% of
OL,7,Fpeople do not understand what a carbon
OL,8,Ffootprint is, while 25% said they
OL,9,Fwould change their diet if they knew
OL,10,Fmore about its carbon impact.
OL,12,FCost appears to be a major barrier to
OL,13,Fsustainable eating, with 32% citing
OL,14,Fmoney as an issue.
OL,16,FHowever, 24% said they are more likely
OL,17,Fto buy a product if it comes in
OL,18,Fsustainable packaging, and 23%
OL,19,Fconsider it important for their food
OL,20,Fchoices to be sustainable.
